                    <desc>
                    red yarn laid in the codex between <locus target="#20 #21" facs="031">folss. 20, 21, </locus>, <locus target="#24 #25" facs="035">24, 25, </locus>, and <locus target="#27 #28" facs="038">27, 28</locus>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#1r #2r #2v #16r #19r" facs="011 012 013 026 029">folss. 1r, 2r, 2v, 16r, 19r, </locus>, etc.);
                      words of text are writen in the upper margin with a symbol (┬) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#1v #139r" facs="012 149">1v, 139r, </locus>), and in another case where the symbol (+) is used (<locus target="#16r #25r #27r #139v #140r" facs="026 035 037 150">16r, 25r, 27r, 139v, 140r, </locus>), and in another case where the symbol (┴) is used (<locus target="#26v #144r #148r" facs="037 154 158">26v, 144r, 148r, </locus>);
